You are working on DineFlow, a full-stack restaurant management SaaS.

# Stack
- Frontend: Next.js 16, TypeScript, Tailwind CSS, Framer Motion, Recharts, Lucide React
- Backend: Express.js, Node.js, Mongoose, MongoDB
- Auth: JWT stored in localStorage

# Code rules
- Always use TypeScript with proper types — never use `any`
- Always use async/await, never .then()
- Use functional components with hooks only — no class components
- All components go in frontend/components/
- All pages go in frontend/app/
- All API calls go through frontend/lib/api.ts
- Backend routes go in backend/routes/

# Design rules
- Primary color: #FF6B00 (orange)
- Dark panels: #0F1115
- Border radius: minimum 20px on cards and modals
- Typography: Inter for body, SF Pro Display for headings
- Use Framer Motion for all animations — no CSS transitions
- Use Tailwind only — never write inline styles

# Patterns
- Always handle loading and error states in every component
- Use the dual-mode store (frontend/lib/store.ts) for all data — never fetch directly in components
- Seed data must match mock data structure exactly
- All forms must validate before submitting